## 1. Layout & Structure

### 1.1 — [BOTH VIEWS] Editor workspace fixed height clips content

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [editor.css:2](file:///c:/Users/josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/editor.css#L2) |
| **What is broken** | `.editor-workspace` has `height: 488px` — a hardcoded pixel value. On shorter screens (<900px tall) content overflows without scrolling; on larger screens it leaves dead space. |
| **Why** | Fixed height doesn't adapt to viewport. There's no `overflow` set on the container itself, only on child panes. |
| **Fix** | Change to viewport-relative height with a minimum: |

```diff
-.editor-workspace { display: flex; height: 488px; background: var(--bg1); }
+.editor-workspace { display: flex; height: calc(100dvh - 100px); min-height: 400px; background: var(--bg1); }
```

