### 1.3 — [DESKTOP ONLY] ATS drawer slides off-screen with `right: -100%`

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [editor.css:50](file:///c:/Users/josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/editor.css#L50) |
| **What is broken** | `.ats-drawer` uses `right: -100%` which moves it relative to its *parent width*, not its own 36% width. This means when closed, the element still generates a large invisible area, potentially causing horizontal scrollbar flicker. |
| **Why** | `right: -100%` references the containing block's width, not the drawer's width. Since the drawer is 36% wide, it only needs to move 36% to hide. |
| **Fix** | Use `transform: translateX(100%)` pattern instead: |

```diff
-.ats-drawer { position: absolute; top: 0; right: -100%; width: 36%; ... transition: right .25s; ... }
-.ats-drawer.open { right: 0; }
+.ats-drawer { position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; width: 36%; ... transition: transform .25s; transform: translateX(100%); ... }
+.ats-drawer.open { transform: translateX(0); }
```

