## 2. Responsive Design

### 2.1 — [MOBILE ONLY] No font import — Plus Jakarta Sans and Inter not loaded

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | All HTML `<head>` sections + [tokens.css:4-6](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/tokens.css#L4-L6) |
| **What is broken** | `--font-headline: "Plus Jakarta Sans"` and `--font-body: "Inter"` are declared as CSS variables but **no Google Fonts `<link>` or `@import`** is included anywhere. On systems without these fonts installed locally, the browser falls back to generic `sans-serif`, causing inconsistent typography across devices—most noticeable on mobile. |
| **Why** | Font declarations exist in tokens.css but the actual font files are never loaded. |
| **Fix** | Add to every HTML `<head>` (or at the top of tokens.css): |

```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

