## 6. Images & Icons

### 6.1 — [BOTH VIEWS] Images missing explicit width/height causing layout shift

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **Files** | All `<img>` tags across index.html, about.html |
| **What is broken** | None of the `<img>` elements specify `width` and `height` attributes. As images load, they cause Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) as the browser doesn't know the dimensions ahead of time. |
| **Why** | No intrinsic sizing declared on image elements. |
| **Fix** | Add `width` and `height` attributes to all images (matching their natural dimensions) or use `aspect-ratio` in CSS on the container. |

