### 6.2 — [BOTH VIEWS] Builder photo in about page uses `min-height` without aspect ratio control

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [public.css:327-334](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/public.css#L327-L334) |
| **What is broken** | `.pub-builder-photo` and its `img` both have `min-height: 300px`. If the image is shorter than 300px, it gets stretched. If it's much taller, there's no max-height constraint. |
| **Why** | Using `min-height` on both container and image without `object-fit` or aspect-ratio prevents proper image scaling. |
| **Fix** | Add `max-height` and rely on object-fit: |

```css
.pub-builder-photo {
  min-height: 200px;
  max-height: 400px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}
.pub-builder-photo img {
  min-height: 0;
  max-height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}
```

