### 9.3 — [BOTH VIEWS] `!important` overuse in layout.css media queries

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [layout.css:203-222](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/layout.css#L203-L222) |
| **What is broken** | Media queries use `display: block !important` and `display: none !important` to toggle desktop/mobile frames. While functional, `!important` makes it impossible to programmatically hide a frame via JS if needed (e.g., for transitions or conditional logic). |
| **Why** | The dual-frame architecture requires forced visibility control. |
| **Fix** | Long-term: move to a single responsive DOM. Short-term: acceptable but be aware of the constraint. |

