### 9.4 — [BOTH VIEWS] Over-applying all CSS to all pages (unnecessary bloat)

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **Files** | [dashboard.html:7-17](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/dashboard.html#L7-L17) (and similar in resumes.html, jds.html, profile.html, editor.html) |
| **What is broken** | Every workspace page loads **all** CSS files (dashboard.css, resumes.css, editor.css, jds.css, profile.css) even when only one page is active. This means unused CSS rules are parsed and held in memory on every page load. |
| **Why** | Simplified approach during modularization — include everything everywhere. |
| **Fix** | Each page should only include its own CSS plus shared files. For example, `dashboard.html` doesn't need `editor.css`, `jds.css`, or `profile.css`. |

