### 9.5 — [BOTH VIEWS] Missing `text-align: center` on `.mob-et-btn` for anchor tags

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [public.css:533-538](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/public.css#L533-L538) |
| **What is broken** | The public pages use `<a class="mob-et-btn">` while workspace pages use `<button class="mob-et-btn">`. Public.css adds a rule `mob-edit-toggle a.mob-et-btn { text-decoration: none; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center }` to compensate. This works but is a specificity workaround — the base `.mob-et-btn` class in mobile.css doesn't center text for `<a>` tags naturally because `<a>` doesn't have `display: flex` by default. |
| **Why** | Class was designed for `<button>` which centers text by default. |
| **Fix** | Add `text-align: center` to the base `.mob-et-btn` rule in mobile.css: |

```diff
 .mob-et-btn {
   flex: 1;
   padding: 6px;
+  text-align: center;
 ```

