### 10.4 — [MOBILE ONLY] `mob-bottom-sheet` bottom position depends on bottombar height

| Detail | |
|---|---|
| **File** | [mobile.css:316](file:///c:/Users/Josep/Desktop/Resume_Project/Prototype_v2/css/mobile.css#L316) |
| **What is broken** | `.mob-bottom-sheet` positions itself with `bottom: calc(58px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom))` to sit above the bottom bar. But if the bottom bar height changes (e.g. text wraps, font loading changes size), the sheet may overlap or leave a gap. |
| **Why** | Hardcoded 58px doesn't dynamically link to the actual bottom bar height. |
| **Fix** | Acceptable for now since the bottombar height is consistently 58px. Add a CSS custom property for maintainability: |

```css
:root {
  --bottombar-height: 58px;
}
```

